# Testing Rules

## Coverage
- Unit tests for core business logic, services, hooks, utilities.
- Avoid testing implementation details.

## Test Structure
- Arrange → Act → Assert
- One logical expectation per test if possible.

## UI Testing
- Focus on behavior and user interactions.
- Do not test styling.

## Memory Leak Prevention
- Clean up event listeners, subscriptions, timers, intervals.
- Hooks must return cleanup functions.
- Long-running resources must be disposed.

## Deprecated Components Detection
- Tests must detect and avoid deprecated components/APIs.
- Replace outdated code immediately.

## Test Isolation
- Use mocks for external APIs and databases.
- Ensure deterministic tests.
